commentTextItems.html: pumped up and over long-on, plugs in the deep, trickles to the rope, and England have secured a tremendous win

commentPostTextItems.html: 9.02pm Right, that's your lot. Thanks for joining us today, have a read of Dan Brettig's report and join us again on Sunday for the third ODI in Sydney, where Australia desperately need a win to stay alive in the series.

Sarvesh : "Even without Stokes, England ODI side is a force to reckon with. They were the most competitive in India among visiting teams last year, after South Africa. They played really well in South Africa before that. I m in favour of a whitewash in Australia !!! " Watch this space. They are clearly a team in a very good frame of mind at the moment. Good night.

9pm Man of the Match is Joe Root for his wickets and runs. "Enjoyable today, didn't think I'd bowl seven overs at the start of the day. The form Smith has been in this summer, very enjoyable to see the back of him."
"Whenever you come off a series loss you want to prove a point, and leading into the World Cup we want to set a benchmark. We had to stay cool in the moment and get the job done."
Eoin Morgan: "Our bowlers were exceptional. It puts pressure on the Australia batsmen. We did enough to win but it was far from a complete performance, which is exciting for us."
"We have a level of trust and confidence in the group that someone will put their hand up for us."

8.55pm Time for some presentations. Here's Steve Smith. "We're not playing good enough one-day cricket at the moment. It's a quality England batting line-up. We lost a couple of wickets in a row, we couldn't get that power going at the back end to get that 320 we were after."
"Richo bowled pretty well, perhaps [we should have played a spinner]. This wicket is different to the one we had for the Test match."
8.47pm England have won their first ODI at Brisbane since 1999, and they have taken an emphatic 2-0 lead without really being stretched in two apparently daunting chases.
Hypocaust: "Joe Root now has the 3rd highest average (87.06) in victorious ODI chases (min. 20 innings), behind Dhoni (102.72) and Kohli (93.64) and just ahead of Bevan (86.25)."

Mark: "Are we facing a scenario where Australia's total domination of the Tests will be countered by England's total domination of the ODIs and T20s. You begin to wonder if Australia could be whitewashed."

Deedat: "Like Morgan said last time, if Roy fails, someone from the rest of the team would step up. This time, seems like who whole team did. Magnificent from Hales and Bairstow. And just solid as always from Root"

commentTextItems.html: up and over point, leaning back and timing the pants off his uppercut! Scores are level...

commentPostTextItems.html: David: "So, in the end, we're looking at Joe Root utterly failing to convert. "

commentTextItems.html: up and over the covers, a shackle-breaking slap to reduce the requirement to within a single blow

commentPostTextItems.html: England are easing towards the finish line... but the Alexis Sanchez transfer saga still has legs. Will he sign for Manchester United today? Or will Peter Crouch take the headlines by rocking up at Chelsea? Follow the madness over on Transfer Talk at ESPNFC

commentPostTextItems.html: Mukunda Phuyal: "Root justifying the value of keeping wicket and at times ticking the scoreboard. This is a typical one day old fashioned match winning innings from him." Every team needs a nurdler. Even the pedal to the metal ones

commentPostTextItems.html: AshesAddict: "Going back to 2005 (with the sole exception of 2013/14), the team winning the Ashes tests series has then failed to win the following ODI series. Good omen for England?" I suppose it is. If you discount the fact that the team that has lost most of those ODI series is England!

dismissalText.commentary: David Warner c Root b Ali 35 (40b 5x4 0x6) SR: 87.5

dismissalComment.html: edged, taken! Lovely stuff from Moeen. This is tighter to off stump, Warner looking to push into the off side, takes an outside edge and snaffled at slip

dismissalText.commentary: Steven Smith lbw b Root 18 (25b 0x4 1x6) SR: 72

dismissalComment.html: huge appeal and Smith is pinned lbw! Unsurprisingly, he has reviewed... he was stretching onto the front foot, might it have hit him outside the line? Nope, that is trimming the top of the leg bail and what a breakthrough!

dismissalText.commentary: Travis Head c & b Root 7 (18b 0x4 0x6) SR: 38.88

dismissalComment.html: Root has another! This is a killer spell! Head lost his head, charging down the pitch but beaten in the flight, a tame popped return catch, and Australia's innings has been blown wide open by the part-timer!

headshotImage.caption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Marsh st Buttler b Rashid 36 (43b 3x4 0x6) SR: 83.72

dismissalComment.html: he's gone now! He knew he had to press the accelerator, he charges out of his crease, nowhere near the ball, has a swing across the line, misses and it's a simple stumping for Buttler

dismissalText.commentary: Aaron Finch c Roy b Plunkett 106 (114b 9x4 1x6) SR: 92.98

dismissalComment.html: finds mid-on! Once again, England strike back-to-back...went to drive down the ground, think he wanted to go over top, got no sort of elevation and it's a simple catch on the edge of the circle

dismissalText.commentary: Marcus Stoinis c Buttler b Rashid 4 (6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: given caught behind! That's a lovely piece of bowling, England on the charge. Floated up on off stump, draws Stonis forward, spins away as he drives and it's a thin snick

dismissalText.commentary: Alex Carey run out (Woakes) 27 (24b 4x4 0x6) SR: 112.5

dismissalComment.html: that's why England warm-up with football! Great skills from Woakes. Superb from him all-round, in fact. Firstly he out-smarted White with a slower-ball bouncer which was bottom edged into the crease, Carey came through for the run, Woakes followed through and right-footed into the stumps

headshotImage.caption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Starc c Roy b Woakes 3 (6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: this time he's taken at deep midwicket! Roy this time. Good length, bit of pace off, Starc tries to clear the leg side and can't get the distance needed

dismissalText.commentary: Andrew Tye run out (Woakes) 8 (4b 0x4 1x6) SR: 200

dismissalComment.html: direct hit! Dot ball and a wicket to end. Woakes goes short, Tye bottom edges into the crease, they go for the run, Woakes is quickly on it in his follow through then spins around and hits direct at the non-striker's end

dismissalText.commentary: Jason Roy c Finch b Starc 2 (4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: flicked off the toes, and scooped up at short midwicket! It was the swing wot won it, aiming straight, looking for the lbw, Roy's bat came swishing across the line but couldn't stay on top of the shot. A good low grab from Finch to lift Australia's spirits

dismissalText.commentary: Jonny Bairstow c Warner b Richardson 60 (56b 9x4 0x6) SR: 107.14

dismissalComment.html: finds cover! Back-to-back wickets for Richardson. Full outside off, he goes for the drive, neither keeps it down or goes fully over the top, picks out Warner

headshotImage.caption: Jhye Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jhye Richardson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Alex Hales b Richardson 57 (60b 7x4 1x6) SR: 95

dismissalComment.html: dragged on! A first ODI wicket for Richardson. Short of a length, looking to run it down to third man and gets an under edge into the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root not out 46 (58b 1x4 0x6) SR: 79.31
Eoin Morgan b Starc 21 (27b 2x4 1x6) SR: 77.77

dismissalComment.html: he's done it! Via the inside edge. Game on? A good length ball, just angling into Morgan, playing forward, gets an inside edge into his pad then into the stumps

headshotImage.caption: Alex Carey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Alex Carey player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jos Buttler c Carey b Starc 42 (32b 5x4 0x6) SR: 131.25

dismissalComment.html: edged and gone! Through to the keeper, easy as pie. That's a superb ball in any circumstance. Angled in, nipping away, drawing the thin edge. A glimmer

dismissalText.commentary: Moeen Ali b Starc 1 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: there it goes! This is brilliant from Starc ... so full, so quick, late movement with reverse into the toes. Moeen's timbers are rattled and, well, he's not given up the ghost yet!

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Woakes not out 39 (27b 5x4 1x6) SR: 144.44
